-- Iran Lawmakers Seek to Impeach Minister for Inflation, Fars Says
-- B y   Y e g a n e h   S a l e h i
-- 2012-07-22T12:18:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-22/iran-lawmakers-seek-to-impeach-minister-for-inflation-fars-says.html
A group of 20 Iranian lawmakers are
seeking to impeach Industries, Mines and Commerce Minister Mehdi
Ghazanfari for his alleged inability to prevent inflation from
taking hold in the country’s markets,  Fars  reported.  “Rising prices in our society and problems this has
caused” are the reasons for the impeachment motion that has
been signed by 20 lawmakers, Fathollah Hosseini, a member of the
parliament, told the state-run  news agency  in a report published
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yeganeh Salehi in Dubai at 
